before.enText: often in the names of streets

data.enText: a continuous row of similar houses that are joined together in one block

data.chText: （尤指房屋或餐馆外的）露天平台，阳台
data.enText: a flat, hard area, especially outside a house or restaurant, where you can sit, eat and enjoy the sun

data.chText: 所有的房间都有阳台或露台。
data.enText: All rooms have a balcony or terrace.
the wide steps at a football ( soccer ) ground where people can stand to watch the game
one of a series of flat areas of ground that are cut into the side of a hill like steps so that crops can be grown there

simple_means.memory_skill: terr 地 + ace 抽象名词及实物名词 → 如平原之地 → 平台

means: (尤指房屋或餐馆外的)露天平台，阳台

tr: usually paved outdoor area adjoining a residence
a row of houses built in a similar style and having common dividing walls (or the street on which they face)
a level shelf of land interrupting a declivity (with steep slopes above and below)
make into terraces as for cultivation
example: The Incas terraced their mountainous land

value.def: A terrace is a row of similar houses joined together by their side walls.

example.tran: 一排雅致的维多利亚风格的房屋

value.tran: 排屋(指相互连接、式样相似的房屋)

value.def: A terrace is a flat area of stone or grass next to a building where people can sit.

example.ex: Some guests recline in lounge chairs on the sea-facing terrace.
example.tran: 在面向大海的平台上一些客人斜躺在躺椅上。

value.def: Terraces are a series of flat areas built like steps on the side of a hill so that crops can be grown there.

example.ex: ...massive terraces of maize and millet carved into the mountainside like giant steps.
example.tran: 山坡上开垦出的像巨型台阶一样的大块大块梯田，上面种着玉米和小米

value.def: The terraces at a football ground are wide steps that people can stand on when they are watching a game.
value.tran: (足球赛观众可站立的)阶梯看台

dis 除去 + inter 埋葬 → 把埋进去的挖出来 → 挖出
extra 以外 + terrestrial 地球的，陆地的 → 地球外的
medi 中间 + terr 土地 + ane …的 + al …的 → 在陆地中间的 → 被陆地包围的
medi 中间 + terr 土地 + ane 有…性质的 + an 属于…地方的 → 被陆地包围的一片海洋 → 地中海
sub 下 + terr 土地 + ane 表物 → 下面的地方 → 地下室
terr 土地 + ace 表实物名词 → 平台；梯田
terr 土地 + ain 表物 → 地形；地域
terr 土地 + estr + ial …的 → 地球的，陆地的
territor〔y〕领土，领域 + ial 具有…的，属于…的 → 领土的
terri 土地 + tory 场所 → 地的范围 → 领地
de 使… + ter〔= terr〕怕；恐吓 → 恐吓 → 阻止
deter 威吓；阻止 + ment 表名词 → 制止
de 使… + terr 怕；恐吓 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 威慑的
terr 怕；恐吓 + ible 可…的 → 可怕的
terr 怕；恐吓 + ific 产生…的 → 好得可怕 → 极好的
terr 怕；恐吓 + ify 使 → 恐吓
terr 怕；恐吓 + or 表人 → 恐怖；引起恐怖的人（或事）
